The importance of mobile computing is rapidly increasing with the current trend of universalization of computer networking and wireless communication . The proposed workshop intends to bring together the researchers and practitioners working on diverse aspects of this important area in order to identify current status , fundamental issues , future problems and applications . We 'd invite papers describing both theoretical and experimental research as well as experience reports and position papers . Topics will include , but are not limited to : Mobile Ad Hoc Network ( routing , medium access control ) Location-aware Mobile Environments and Applications Security in Wireless Communication Mobility-tolerant communication protocols Wireless web browsing Location management & Data management Distributed resource ( channel ) allocation Resilience against mobile faults ( malicious agents ) Wireless application architecture , languages and protocols Multimedia in mobile environments Modeling and simulations of wireless data networks Original papers describing ongoing or completed research and development efforts are sought . Submissions must not exceed 10 pages in length . The accepted papers will be published in the workshop proceedings . Interested authors should electronically mail a PDF file or a Postscript ( ghostviewable ) file of the paper to Sandeep K S Gupta , Department of Computer Science , Colorado State University , Ft . Collins , CO 80523 USA , Voice : + 970 491 - 7323 , Fax : + 970 491 - 2466 , Email : gupta @ xgt . lt . rqh . If electronic submission is not possible , please send five hardcopies .
